    "body": "We're following python's lead and using its implementation - `Series.str.is[]` will always do the same as `str.is[]`.  Apparently the difference between `isdecimal` and `isdigit` is that that the latter is more expansive with respect to non ASCII digits, so this is working as expected.\r\n\r\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/22789392/str-isdecimal-and-str-isdigit-difference-example\r\n```python\r\na = '5'\r\n\r\na.isdecimal(), a.isdigit()\r\nOut[102]: (True, True)\r\n\r\nb = 'Â²'  # '\\u00B2'\r\n\r\nb.isdecimal(), b.isdigit()\r\nOut[104]: (False, True)\r\n```"
